20and%20software%20for%20the%20Vision%20Pro%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20product%20nobody%20needs%20and%20solving%20problems%20no%20one%20has.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Apple%20has%20been%20neither%20a%20leader%20nor%20a%20follower%20on%20useful%20smartphone%20innovations%20such%20as%20folding%20phones%2C%20which%20allow%20users%20to%20have%20both%20a%20small%20phone%20and%20a%20larger%20screen%20in%20one%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20truth%20is%2C%20there's%20a%20very%20good%20reason%20why%20Apple%20doesn't%20do%20drastic%20changes%20to%20its%20products%3A%20slow%2C%20steady%20and%20reliable%20products%20are%20keeping%20Apple%20on%20top.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20fair%2C%20under%20CEO%20Tim%20Cook%2C%20Apple%20has%20had%20several%20big%20hit%20new%20products%3A%20Apple%20Watch%20and%20Air%20Pods%2C%20come%20to%20mind.%20Although%20I've%20also%20argued%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-new-products-ar-vr-glasses-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboth%20of%20those%20are%20really%20iPhone%20accessories%3C%2Fa%3E%20since%20Watch%20won't%20pair%20with%20a%20non-iOS%20device.%20While%20Air%20Pods%20will%20work%20with%20others%2C%20they%20are%20really%20designed%20to%20work%20best%20with%20Apple%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20Steve%20Jobs%20era%2C%20in%20the%20Cook%20era%2C%20Apple%20does%20not%20often%20release%20new%20products%20that%20are%20radically%20different%20from%20previous%20versions.%20It%20tends%20to%20focus%20on%20making%20incremental%20improvements%20to%20existing%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20that%20boring%3F%20Yes%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flifehacker.com%2Fiphone-15-pro-max-review-1850887664%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eas%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.macworld.com%2Farticle%2F2113408%2Fits-samsungs-fault-the-apple-watch-is-boring.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Emany%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.laptopmag.com%2Ffeatures%2Fmacbook-air-15-is-the-most-boring-apple-laptop-in-years-i-hate-that-i-want-one%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etech%20press%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20besides%20me%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.phonearena.com%2Fnews%2Fboring-looking-iphone-15-and-iphone-15-pro-apple-does-not-see-color-problem_id150356%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ealso%20noted%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20it%20also%20means%20that%20Apple%20products%20are%20very%20consistent%20and%20therefore%20very%20reliable%20and%20hold%20their%20value.%20That's%20rather%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsers%20want%20consistency.%20They%20don't%20want%20to%20learn%20new%20ways%20of%20doing%20the%20things%20they%20already%20do%2C%20just%20because%20the%20device%20maker%20is%20attempting%20to%20be%20novel%20by%20moving%20everything%20around.%20(Microsoft%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2FOffice365%2Fcomments%2F14xrkxc%2Fwhy_wtf_does_microsoft_keep_moving_and_renaming%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eoften%20been%20accused%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20that.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ferraris%20are%20cool%20cars%2C%20the%20farthest%20thing%20from%20a%20boring%20product%20in%20any%20way%2C%20most%20of%20us%20will%20never%20buy%20one%20(VCs%20who%20funded%20Humane'%20Ai%20Pin%20excluded).%20Most%20of%20us%20will%20spend%20our%20money%20on%20a%20Honda%20sedan%20or%20a%20Ford%20truck%20or%2C%20if%20we%20have%20the%20budget%2C%20a%20BMW%20or%20Tesla.%20We'll%20choose%20something%20that%20looks%20good%2C%20is%20reliable%2C%20safe%2C%20functional%20for%20our%20needs%20and%20will%20hold%20its%20value%20over%20time.%20Ever%20try%20to%20trade%20in%20your%20Android%20phone%3F%20You'll%20likely%20get%20far%20less%20for%20most%20models%20than%20you%20would%20if%20you%20had%20traded%20in%20an%20iPhone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20I%20know%20from%20my%20years%20as%20a%20market%20researcher%20and%20my%20time%20working%20at%20Apple%20during%20the%20Jobs%20era%2C%20is%20that%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20users%20won't%20pay%20money%20for%20flashy%20new%20tech%20that%20doesn't%20add%20something%20useful%20to%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20industry%20is%20buzzing%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20about%20the%20new%20Humane%20Ai%20Pin%2C%20a%20%24600%20gadget%20(plus%20a%20%2424%20monthly%20subscription%20fee)%20that%20is%20intended%20to%20be%20a%20smartphone%20replacement.%20It%20clips%20to%20your%20clothes%2C%20has%20been%20showcased%20by%20fashion%20models%20in%20Milan%20and%20looks%20super%20cool.%20While%20this%20device%20may%20have%20been%20developed%20by%20former%20Apple%20employees%20this%20is%20the%20most%20un-Apple%20product%20I%20have%20ever%20seen.%20It's%20another%20product%20looking%20for%20a%20solution%2C%20and%2C%20with%20its%20camera%20and%20use%20of%20AI%2C%20is%20a%20privacy%20conundrum%2C%20too.%20I%20predict%20it%20ends%20up%20in%20the%20gadget%20hall%20of%20shame%20next%20to%20Juicero%20and%20Microsoft%20Kin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Apple%20products%20are%20designed%20with%20a%20minimalist%20and%20modern%20aesthetic%20and%20most%20importantly%20(Vision%20Pro%20aside)%20a%20user's%20needs.%20They%20are%20made%20with%20high-quality%20materials%20and%20have%20a%20sleek%20and%20stylish%20look.%20Because%20Apple%20doesn't%20change%20much%20over%20time%2C%20the%20iPhone's%20design%20has%20become%20classic%20and%20iconic.%20Same%20for%20the%20Macbook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExamples%20of%20other%20classic%20products%20with%20looks%20that%20haven't%20changed%20much%20over%20time%20include%20the%20Rolex%20Submariner%2C%20which%20today%20still%20looks%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20as%20when%20007%20wore%20his%20in%20the%201962%20film%20%3Cem%3EDr.%20No%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Another%20example%3A%20the%20Porsche%20911%2C%20the%20Coca-Cola%20glass%20bottle%2C%20Sperry%20Docksiders.%20I%20could%20go%20on%2C%20but%20the%20point%20is%20clear.%20Iconic%20designs%20sell%20well%20for%20decades.%20Goofy%20designs%20usually%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20Apple's%20case%2C%20it%20can%20even%20make%20goofy%20products%20look%20cool.%20Apple%20has%20made%20walking%20around%20with%20what%20appear%20to%20be%20cigarette%20butts%20sticking%20out%20of%20people's%20ears%20cool.%20The%20AppleWatch%20Ultra%20is%20kind%20of%20big%20and%20clunky%20but%20the%20watch%20is%20so%20aspirational%20that%20it's%20become%20popular%20even%20with%20people%20who%20aren't%20the%20target%20market%20of%20runners%2C%20explorers%2C%20divers%20and%20the%20like.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20worn%20on%20the%20wrists%20of%20people%20like%20me%20who%20just%20like%20the%20fact%20that%20it's%20lightweight%2C%20has%20a%20large%20screen%2C%20great%20battery%20life.%20And%20it%20also%20makes%20people%20who%20see%20it%20on%20me%20think%20I'm%20the%20kind%20of%20person%20who%20free%20dives%20when%20not%20trekking%20across%20the%20Sahara%20(at%20least%20I%20think%20it%20it%20does).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20as%20much%20as%20I%2C%20and%20millions%20of%20others%2C%20admire%20Apple's%20product%20design%20aesthetic%2C%20that%20is%20not%20what%20has%20made%20Apple%20into%20the%20tech%20giant%20it%20is%20today.%20When%20people%20discussed%20who%20could%20be%20the%20heir%20to%20Apple%20after%20Jobs%2C%20the%20most%20talked%20about%20person%20was%20Jony%20Ive.%20After%20all%2C%20he%20was%20Steve's%20%26quot%3Bsoulmate.%26quot%3B%20He%20also%20gave%20us%20nutty%20things%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgold-apple-watch-price-2015-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elike%20%2410%2C000%20Gold%20Apple%20Watches%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapple-butterfly-keyboard-macbook-issues-timeline-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einfamous%20butterfly%20keyboard%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20devices%20so%20minimalist%20the%20designs%20were%20changed%20immediately%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.30pin.com%2Ffeatures%2Fipod-shuffle-3g%2F.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2009%20Apple%20Shuffle%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20no%2C%20it%20was%20then-COO%20Cook%20who%20ascended%2C%20the%20man%20who%20made%20Apple's%20corporate%20mechanisms%20run%20on%20time%2C%20its%20master%20of%20the%20supply%20chain.%20Cook%20wasn't%20known%20for%20creating%20new%20Apple%20products%20(and%20despite%20some%20successes%2C%20still%20isn't).%20He%20isn't%20the%20most%20dynamic%20speaker.%20In%20fact%2C%20his%20presentations%20can%20be%20kind%20of%20dull.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20he%20did%20do%20was%20take%20Apple%20to%20a%20%243%20trillion%20market%20cap%20and%20made%20it%20the%20most%20valued%20company%20in%20the%20world.%20The%20truth%20is%20Apple%20can%20be%20less%20innovative%20and%20more%20incremental%20because%20it%20commands%20such%20a%20large%20and%20loyal%20user%20base%20who%20benefit%20by%20products%20that%20remain%20steady.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20danger%20in%20being%20too%20classic%2C%20too%20slow%20to%20change%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20tech%20industry.%20Apple%20already%20needs%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20parts%20of%20the%20industry%20it%20once%20led%20but%20now%20trails%2C%20like%20AI.%20(I've%20previously%20argued%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapples-ai-strategies-especially-for-siri-not-very-smart-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESiri%20is%20still%20a%20mess%20compared%20to%20Google%20Assistant%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yes%2C%20when%20it%20leans%20away%20from%20serving%20users%20and%20towards%20greed%20(like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapples-app-store-has-become-an-ad-plagued-version-of-its-former-self-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprioritizing%20ads%20in%20its%20app%20store%3C%2Fa%3E)%20or%20protectionism%20(like%20its%20petty%20walled%20garden%20that%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F