ought%20home%20to%20me%20with%20startling%20clarity%20a%20few%20days%20ago%20by%20a%20video%20featuring%20a%20conversation%20between%20the%20Egyptian-American%20comedian%20Bassem%20Youssef%20and%20the%20British%20TV%20talk-show%20host%20Piers%20Morgan%20around%20the%20ongoing%20Gaza%20war.%20This%20conversation%20really%C2%A0%20followed%20upon%20an%20earlier%20TV%20programme%20where%20Morgan%20in%20London%20spoke%20with%20Youssef%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20about%20the%20crisis%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20course%20of%20that%20interview%2C%20Youssef%20had%20spoken%20witheringly%20about%20the%20West%E2%80%99s%20studied%20ambivalence%20on%20the%20Palestine%20question%2C%20ambivalence%20that%20was%20often%20indistinguishable%20from%20moral%20equivocation.%20The%20great%20Western%20democracies%2C%20he%20implied%2C%20were%20unwilling%20or%20unable%2C%20or%20both%2C%20to%20comprehend%20the%20horrendous%20inequities%20Palestinians%20were%20obliged%20to%20suffer%20daily%20at%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMorgan%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20clearly%20felt%20frustrated%20by%20his%20inability%20to%20draw%20Youssef%20into%20an%20excoriation%20of%20what%20Hamas%20stood%20for.%20Perplexed%20by%20Youssef%E2%80%99s%20apparent%20intransigence%2C%20Morgan%20flew%20all%20the%20way%20to%20LA%20a%20few%20days%20later%20and%20buttonholed%20the%20comedian%20for%20a%20lengthy%20chat%20which%20was%20broadcast%20live%20on%20TV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26165755%2FUNI450059.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221093%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26165755%2FUNI450059.jpg%20770w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F1