%20down%20on%20three%20generations%20of%20European%20liberals%20thanks%20to%20the%20memory%20of%20Europe%E2%80%99s%20betrayal%20of%20its%20Jews%20leading%20to%20the%20Holocaust.%20That%20sense%20of%20shame%20perhaps%20found%20a%20vicarious%20egress%20in%20the%20somewhat%20gratuitous%20references%20to%20the%20Holocaust%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20past%20month%20strewn%20across%20Western%20leaders%E2%80%99%20statements.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20fiercest%20attacks%20on%20the%20Jews%20since%20the%20Holocaust%E2%80%9D%20was%20one%20common%20refrain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20surprise%20us%2C%20therefore%2C%20that%20some%20of%20the%20most%20cogent%20assessments%20of%20the%20Palestine%20problem%20and%20of%20the%20power%20asymmetries%20running%20across%20and%20under%20it%20come%20from%20the%20pens%20and%20the%20voices%20of%20non-Zionist%20Jewish%20intellectuals%20and%20activists%20who%20do%20not%20share%20in%20this%20sense%20of%20guilt%20and%20shame.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20listen%20to%20Avraham%20Burg%2C%20once%20a%20central%20figure%20in%20the%20Zionist%20movement%20and%20the%20former%20president%20of%20the%20Israeli%20parliament%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Zionist%20revolution%20rested%20on%20two%20pillars%3A%20the%20thirst%20for%20justice%20and%20the%20respect%20for%20civic%20morality.%20Both%20have%20disappeared.%20The%20Israeli%20nation%20today%20is%20no%20longer%20anything%20but%20a%20shapeless%20mass%20of%20corruption%2C%20of%20oppression%2C%20and%20of%20injustice.%20The%20end%20of%20the%20Zionist%20adventure%20is%20already%20knocking%20at%20our%20door%E2%80%A6%E2%80%A6%20There%20will%20remain%20a%20jewish%20State%20%E2%80%93%20an%20unrecognisable%2C%20detestable%20State.%20After%20our%20two%20thousand%20years%20of%20fighting%20for%20survival%2C%20our%20reality%20is%20a%20colonialist%20State%20under%20the%20yoke%20of%20a%20corrupt%20clique%2C%20a%20State%20that%20makes%20mockery%20of%20legality%20and%20of%20civic%20morality.%20%5BExcerpted%20from%20Michel%20Warschawski%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3C%2Fem%3EToward%20an%20Open%20Tomb%3Cem%3E%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%C2%A0%20Israeli%20journalist-activist%20Michel%20Warschawski%20puts%20his%20finger%20on%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Palestine%20problem%E2%80%9D%20when%20he%20observes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20the%20process%20of%20Israeli%20settlement%2C%20Palestinians%20are%20demoted%20from%20the%20status%20of%20community%20to%20(an)%20environmental%20problem%2C%20which%20has%20to%20be%20moved%20or%20cleaned%20up%20as%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20occupation%20army%20or%20the%20whirlwind%20settlement%20program%20require%E2%80%A6..Since%20the%20beginning%20of%202001%2C%20the%20entire%20Palestinian%20population%20has%20been%20shut%20up%20in%20zones%20and%20micro-zones%2C%20without%20being%20able%20to%20move%20normally%20from%20one%20zone%20to%20the%20next.%20The%20lockdown%20instituted%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%98%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Epeace%20process%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%99%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Ehas%20been%20transformed%20into%20the%20encirclement%20of%20about%20a%20hundred%20towns%20and%20villages%E2%80%A6%20%5BExcerpted%20from%20Michel%20Warschawski%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3C%2Fem%3EToward%20an%20Open%20Tomb%2C%20%3Cem%3Echapter%202%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98A%20Double%20Dehumanization%E2%80%99%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElsewhere%2C%20in%20the%20same%20vein%2C%20Warschawski%20is%20even%C2%A0%20more%20forthright%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESurrender%20or%20get%20out%3A%20this%20is%20the%20choice%20that%20the%20Israeli%20political-military%20class%2C%20for%20whom%20violence%20has%20become%20its%20only%20political%20instrument%2C%20offers%20the%20Palestinians.%20%5BExcerpted%20from%20Michel%20Warschawski%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3C%2Fem%3EToward%20an%20Open%20Tomb%3Cem%3E%2C%20chapter%203%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20New%20Face%20of%20Racism%E2%80%99%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Burg%20and%20Warschawski%20are%20witness%20to%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20current%2021st%20century%20%3Cem%3Eavatar%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20so%20are%20in%20a%20position%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20contemporary%20situation%20there.%20But%20as%20far%20back%20as%20in%201958%20%E2%80%93%20when%20Israel%20was%20celebrating%20its%2010th%20birthday%20%E2%80%93%20the%20great%20Jewish-born%20Marxist%20intellectual%20Isaac%20Deutscher%20wrote%20presciently%20about%20what%20was%20to%20transpire%20decades%20later%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%A6at%20its%20very%20birth%20Israel%20could%20not%20help%20trespassing%20upon%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20Arabs.%20But%20in%20its%20own%20interest%20Israel%20could%20and%20should%20have%20done%20everything%20in%20its%20power%20to%20assuage%20Arab%20grievance%20and%20mitigate%20the%20antagonism.%20Instead%2C%20Israel%20has%20done%20nearly%20everything%20to%20exacerbate%20and%20perpetuate%20the%20antagonism%E2%80%A6.%C2%A0%20In%20the%20balance%20sheet%20of%20Israel%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Es%20first%20decade%20this%20is%20a%20grave%20liability%20which%20may%20in%20time%20outweigh%20many%20impressive%20assets.%20In%20the%20long%20run%2C%20Israel%20cannot%20survive%20on%20the%20borders%20of%20Asia%20and%20Africa%20in%20conflict%20with%20Asia%20and%20Africa.%20Israel%20has%20become%20the%20haven%20of%20refuge%20for%20the%20survivors%20of%20European%20Jewry.%20Let%20it%20not%20become%20a%20death-trap%20for%20them!%20%5BExcerpted%20from%20Deutshcher%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Non-Jewish%20Jew%20and%20other%20essays%2C%3Cem%3E%20chapter%206%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Israel%E2%80%99s%20Tenth%20Birthday%E2%80%99%5D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Western%20liberal%2C%20the%20first%20lesson%20he%20can%20learn%20in%20trying%20to%20be%20true%20to%20his%20liberalism%20is%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20calling%20out%20the%20rogue%20Israeli%20State%20in%20the%2021st%20century%20is%20not%20to%20be%20a%20Holocaust%20denier.%20Equally%2C%20invoking%20the%20Holocaust%2