about%2Fcoronavirus%2F%5C%22%3ECOVID-19%3C%2Fa%3E%20pandemic%2C%20etc.%20were%20used%20to%20%E2%80%9Cinfluence%E2%80%9D%20the%20assembly%20elections%20held%20in%20Punjab%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Fsection%2Fcities%2Fgoa%2F%5C%22%3EGoa%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fexplained%2Fwhat-is-the-delhi-liquor-case-what-are-eds-allegations-against-aap-leaders-8970389%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20early%202022.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20chief%20secretary%20of%20Delhi%2C%20Sharma%20could%20have%20had%20the%20information%20needed%20to%20report%20what%20he%20considered%20%E2%80%9Cirregularities%20in%20procedure%E2%80%9D.%20He%20may%20even%20have%20been%20misled%20by%20his%20officers%20into%20believing%20that%20there%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cheavy%20financial%20losses%20to%20the%20exchequer%E2%80%9D.%20But%20there%20was%20no%20conceivable%20way%20in%20which%20he%20could%20have%20found%20out%20how%20much%20the%20party%2C%20or%20select%20members%20within%20it%2C%20received%20as%20kickbacks%2C%20or%20how%20these%20were%20being%20diverted%20into%20funding%20elections%20in%20other%20states.%20This%20could%20at%20most%20have%20been%20conjecture%2C%20but%20it%20gave%20the%20Modi%20government%20the%20pretext%20it%20wanted%20to%20begin%20its%20onslaught%20on%20the%20AAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Modi%20government%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Fnews%2Fsc-upholds-amendments-to-pmla-giving-ed-unbridled-powers-of-summons-arrests-raids%2Farticle65689464.ece%5C%22%3Ehad%20passed%3C%2Fa%3E%20eight%20amendments%20to%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20in%202019%20that%20gave%20the%20ED%20virtually%20unlimited%20powers%20of%20arrest%20and%20incarceration.%20The%20amendments%20also%20made%20it%20virtually%20impossible%20for%20indicted%20persons%20to%20obtain%20bail%20%3Cem%3Ewithout%20first%20all-but-proving%20their%20innocence.%3C%2Fem%3E%20So%2C%20all%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20needed%20to%20do%20to%20destroy%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20for%20total%20accountability%20to%20the%20electorate%20was%20to%20accuse%20it%20of%20an%20offence%20under%20the%20PMLA%2C%20send%20the%20members%20of%20its%20government%20directly%20responsible%20for%20the%20policy%20to%20judicial%20custody%2C%20and%20keep%20them%20there%20till%20the%20ordinary%20voter%20was%20convinced%20that%20%3Cem%3Ethey%20had%20to%20have%20committed%20some%20irregularity%20that%20justified%20keeping%20them%20in%20jail%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20tactic%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20been%20using%20against%20his%20opponents%20ever%20since%20he%20has%20begun%20to%20feel%20the%20throne%20on%20which%20he%20sits%20starting%20to%20shake.%20In%20Delhi%2C%20his%20first%20target%20was%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20industry%20minister%20and%20a%20key%20figure%20for%20the%20Himachal%20Pradesh%20assembly%20elections%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fed-arrests-delhi-health-minister-satyendar-jain-in-money-laundering-case%5C%22%3ESatyendar%20Jain.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJain%20was%20considered%20a%20%E2%80%98soft%E2%80%99%20target%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20since%202017%2C%20because%20in%20that%20year%2C%20and%20again%20in%202018%2C%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20had%20investigated%20him%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20finding%20something%20indictable%2C%20but%20had%20failed.%20In%202022%2C%20however%2C%20now%20armed%20with%20the%202019%20amendments%20to%20the%20PMLA%2C%20the%20ED%20was%20able%20to%20not%20only%20arrest%20him%2C%20but%20keep%20him%20in%20jail%20for%2017%20months%20without%20trial%2C%20conviction%20or%20even%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%202024%20elections%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20Modi%20has%20started%20to%20feel%20insecure.%20His%20government%20is%20capitalising%20on%20the%20doubt%20that%20Jain%E2%80%99s%20long%C2%A0%20incarceration%20has%20sown%20in%20ordinary%20peoples%E2%80%99%20minds%20to%20redouble%20its%20attacks%20on%20AAP.%20On%20February%2026%2C%20it%20arrested%20Sisodia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESisodia%2C%20too%2C%20has%20now%20been%20in%20jail%20without%20trial%2C%20constantly%20being%20denied%20bail%2C%20since%20February%2026%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fchronology-samajhiye-5-days-4-agencies-under-modi-govt-control-target-opposition-journalists-activists%5C%22%3EChronology%20Samajhiye%3A%205%20Days%2C%204%20Agencies%20Under%20Modi%20Govt%20Control%20Target%20Opposition%2C%20Journalists%2C%20Activists%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20eight%20months%20that%20have%20followed%2C%20despite%20scores%20of%20searches%2C%20the%20ED%20had%20not%20been%20able%20to%20find%20a%20shred%20of%20evidence%20that%20would%20justify%20keeping%20Sisodia%20in%20jail%20until%20only%20six%20weeks%20ago%2C%20on%20October%205%2C%20when%20it%20arrested%20an%20AAP%20member%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fenforcement-directorate-conducts-searches-at-aap-mp-sanjay-singhs-house%5C%22%3ESanjay%20Singh.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20grounds%20the%20ED%20gave%20for%20his%20arrest%20were%20beyond%20flimsy%2C%20for%20his%20only%20stated%20crime%20was%20that%20he%20introduced%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Delhi%20%E2%80%9CLiquor%20Mafia%E2%80%9D%20to%20Manish%20Sisodia.%20Considering%20how%20many%20people%20a%20politician%20meets%20every%20day%2C%20one%20doubts%20whether%20Sisodia%20even%20remembered%20his%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjay%20Singh%20had%2C%20however%2C%20been%20arrested%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20information%20given%20by%20a%20businessman%20%E2%80%93%20one%20Dinesh%20Arora%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20himself%20under%20arrest%20at%20the%20time%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fdelhi%2Fexcise-policy-case-delhi-court-allows-two-to-turn-approver%2Farticleshow%2F104143419.cms%5C%22%3Ehad%20turned%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20%E2%80%98approver%E2%80%99%20for%20the%20ED.%20The%20ED%20did%20not%20publicise%20the%20reason%20for%20his%20arrest%2C%20but%20admitted%20that%20he%20had%20been%20granted%20freedom%20in%20exchange%20for%20giving%20information%20that%20would%20allow%20the%20Modi%20government%20to%20keep%20Sisodia%20in%20jail%20for%20an%20indefinite%20period%20of%20time.%20This%20was%20necessary%20because%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20bail%20plea%20was%20coming%20up%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20Sisodia%20in%20jail%20was%20essential%20because%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20ultimate%20target%20was%20Arvind%20Kejriwal.%20Having%20sufficiently%20reinforced%20suspicions%20in%20the%20lay%20public%E2%80%99s%20mind%20by%20first%20arresting%20a%20minister%20and%20then%20the%20iconic%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20AAP%20government%2C%20Modi%20was%20about%20to%20unleash%20the%20ED%20on%20Chief%20Minister%20Kejriwal%20himself.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20businessman-turned-informer%20Dinesh%20Arora%E2%80%99s%20willingness%20to%20turn%20approver%20proved%20invaluable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20Arora%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cinformation%E2%80%9D%2C%20Singh%20was%20arrested%20on%20October%205.%20So%20great%20was%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20hurry%20to%20discredit%20Kejriwal%2C%20that%20the%20ED%20issued%20its%20summons%20to%20him%20barely%20three%20weeks%20later.%20To%20say%2C%20therefore%2C%20that%20these%20arrests%20and%20so-called%20%E2%80%98disclosures%E2%80%99%20were%20designed%20to%20destroy%20the%20credibility%20of%20a%20key%20rival%20political%20party%20only%20months%20before%20the%20next%20general%20elections%2C%20would%20therefore%20be%20an%20understatement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fcbi-nia-enforcement-directorate-use-abuse%5C%22%3EThe%20Uses%20(And%20Abuses)%20of%20Investigative%20Agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20truth%20about%20AAP%E2%80%99s%20liquor%20policy%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20remains%20to%20be%20seen%20how%20far%20Prime%20minister%20Modi%20and%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20will%20pursue%20the%20attack%20on%20Kejriwal%20and%20AAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20truth%20about%20the%20new%20liquor%20policy%20that%20the%20Delhi%20government%20introduced%20in%20August%202021%20is%20the%20exact%20opposite%20of%20what%20the%20Modi%20government%20and%20its%20utterly%20tamed%20print%20and%20audio-visual%20media%20outlets%20have%20portrayed%20it%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20%E2%80%98old%E2%80%99%20liquor%20policy%2C%20the%20Delhi%20government%20was%20both%20the%20wholesaler%20and%20the%20retailer%20of%20alcohol%20in%20the%20city.%20The%20government%20paid%20the%20manufacturer%20his%20ex-factory%20price%20plus%205%25%2C%20took%20control%20of%20the%20liquor%20and%20bore%20the%20cost%20of%20transportation%20and%20storage%20till%20the%20retail%20outlets.%20The%20retail%20outlets%20were%20all%20controlled%20by%20the%20government%20but%20licensed%20to%20the%20premise%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20bureaucratic%20wholesale-plus-monopolistic%20retail%20system%20had%20led%20to%20a%20number%20of%20shortcomings%3A%20the%20number%20of%20brands%20of%20any%20particular%20spirit%20stocked%20by%20the%20government%20liquor%20shops%20was%20limited%20and%20not%20responsive%20to%20changes%20in%20public%20tastes%20and%20incomes.%20The%20retail%20liquor%20shops%20were%20unevenly%20distributed%20with%20far%20fewer%20shops%20in%20poorer%20parts%20of%20the%20city.%20Consequently%2C%20a%20greater%20amount%20of%20country%20liquor%20was%20being%20sold%20in%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAAP%E2%80%99s%20new%20policy%20made%20the%20government%20%3Cem%3Eget%20out%20of%20the%20liquor%20trade%20altogether%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20wholesalers%20paid%20a%20tax%20of%2014%25%20on%20their%20sales%20in%20Delhi.%20The%20retail%20trade%20was%20wholly%20privatised%3A%20The%20government%20had%20divided%20the%20city%20into%2032%20zones%2C%20of%20which%2020%20were%20classified%20as%20affluent%2C%20and%20the%20remaining%2012%20as%20relatively%20poor.%20Each%20zone%20was%20divided%20into%20a%20number%20of%20principalities%2C%20each%20to%20be%20served%20by%20up%20to%20three%20retail%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20decided%20the%20number%20of%20retail%20locations%20and%20principalities%20in%20each%20zone%20and%20put%20these%20up%20for%20auction.%20The%20retail%20locations%20were%20evenly%20spaced%20to%20ensure%20that%20every%20%3Cem%3Emohalla%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20every%20section%20of%20the%20population%2C%20had%20equal%20access%20to%20a%20liquor%20shop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20then%20auctioned%20the%20liquor%20shop%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20auction%2C%20the%20government%20garnered%20Rs%205%2C300%20crore%20from%20the%20auction%20of%20locations%20in%20the%20more%20affluent%2020%20zones%2C%20and%20Rs%203%2C180%20crore%20from%20the%20auctions%20in%20the%20remaining%2012%20zones.%20The%20lower%20paying%20capacity%20of%20the%20poorer%20areas%20was%20automatically%20reflected%20in%20the%20lower%20bids%20for%20these%20locations.%20An%20important%20side%20benefit%20of%20the%20new%20policy%20was%20that%20by%20giving%20easier%20access%20to%20licensed%20liquor%20in%20poor%20areas%2C%20it%20reduced%20the%20sale%20of%20illicit%20liquor%20within%20those%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20months%20after%20the%20new%C2%A0%20policy%20came%20into%20operation%2C%20a%20civil%20servant%2C%20who%20withheld%20his%20name%20while%20sharing%20the%20above%20figures%20to%20%3Cem%3EHindustan%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-excise-revenue-set-to-double-after-licence-auctions-under-new-liquor-policy-101628274483032.html%5C%22%3Etold%20its%20correspondent%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20along%20with%20new%20brand%20licensing%20and%20some%20other%20minor%20taxes%2C%20the%20government%20expected%20to%20garner%20over%20Rs%2010%2C000%20crore%20a%20year%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20liquor%20in%20the%20capital.%20This%20was%20almost%20double%20the%20average%20of%20Rs%205%2C500-crore%20recorded%20in%20the%20previous%20three%20years%2C%20and%20the%20excise%20revenue%20of%20Rs%205%2C272%20crore%20(excluding%20VAT)%20that%20was%20garnered%20between%20September%201%2C%202022%20and%20August%2031%2C%202023%20after%20the%20return%20to%20the%20old%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20entire%20liquor%20trade%20was%20privatised%2C%20and%20all%20allotments%20were%20made%20through%20public%20auction%2C%20where%20did%20the%20space%20remain%20for%20graft%20and%20favouritism%3F%20In%20the%2018%20months%20since%20Jain%20was%20imprisoned%2C%20no%20newspaper%20has%20asked%20this%20question.%20The%20omission%20speaks%20volumes%20for%20the%20moral%20decay%20that%20has%20settled%20into%20journalism%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn2%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-hounding-of-the-aam-aadmi-party%23_ftnref2%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700308805000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F02%2F18161034%2FScreen-Shot-2020-02-18-at-4.08.52-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-hounding-of-the-aam-aadmi-party%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20his%20first%20year%20in%20office%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20targeted%20every%20political%20leader%2C%20every%20political%20party%2C%20and%20every%20institution%20that%20could%20become%20a%20threat%20to%20his%20ambition.%20Paradoxically%2C%20the%20party%20he%20seems%20to%20fear%20the%20most%20is%20the%20smallest%20among%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20major%20constituents%20%E2%80%93%20%C2%A0the%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthe-houn