ad-shah-fresh-charges%5C%22%3Ewas%20held%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20charges%20of%20terrorism%20for%20publishing%20the%20article%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EThe%20shackles%20of%20slavery%20will%20break%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20his%20now-defunct%20magazine%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%202011.%20The%20opinion%20piece%20was%20authored%20by%20Aala%20Fazili%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Kashmir%20scholar%20who%20has%20also%20been%20arrested%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%E2%80%99s%20counsel%20and%20senior%20advocate%20P.N.%20Raina%20said%20that%20the%20court%20quashed%20the%20charges%20under%20Sections%2018%20(terror%20conspiracy)%20and%20121%20(waging%20war%20against%20the%20country)%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20and%20153-B%20(imputations%2C%20assertions%20prejudicial%20to%20national-integration)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20against%20Shah.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHe%20(Shah)%20will%20face%20trial%20under%20Section%2013%20(abetting%20unlawful%20activities)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20and%20Sections%2035%20(receiving%20foreign%20funds%20illegally)%20and%2039%20(offences%20by%20companies)%20under%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20(Regulation)%20Act%2C%202010%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raina%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20case%20was%20filed%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20State%20Investigation%20Agency%20at%20the%20CIJ%20police%20station%20in%20Jammu%20on%20April%204%2C%202022%20(FIR%20No%3A%2001%2F2022)%2C%20around%2011%20years%20after%20Fazili%E2%80%99s%20piece%20appeared%20in%20the%20magazine.%20A%20chargesheet%20was%20filed%20in%20the%20case%20last%20year%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20April%20this%20year%2C%20the%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ffahad-shah-public-safety-act-jammu-kashmir-high-court%5C%22%3Ehad%20quashed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20Public%20Safety%20Act%20(PSA)%20invoked%20against%20Shah%20by%20terming%20the%20allegations%20of%20the%20J%26amp%3BK%20administration%20as%20%E2%80%9Cmere%20surmise%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cvague%20and%20bald%20assertions%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20accused%20the%20authorities%20of%20snatching%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cconstitutional%20and%20legal%20rights%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnestyusa.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F04%2Fasa200012011en_11.pdf%5C%22%3EAmnesty%20International%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20PSA%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Clawless%20law%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20has%20been%20used%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Crevolving%20door%E2%80%9D%20policy%20for%20suspects%20against%20whom%20the%20government%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20has%20little%20or%20no%20evidence%20to%20bring%20formal%20charges%20against%20them%20in%20the%20court%20of%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%E2%80%99s%20PSA%20dossier%2C%20accessed%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20alleged%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Cfilled%20with%20hatred%20against%20%5Bthe%5D%20Union%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cpromoted%20separatism%E2%80%9D.%20It%20further%20alleged%20that%20his%20%E2%80%9Cactivities%20seem%20to%20be%20prejudicial%20to%20the%20sovereignty%2C%20security%2C%20integrity%2C%20peace%20and%20tranquility%20of%20the%20UT%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20also%20the%20Union%20of%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dossier%20also%20accused%20Shah%20of%20arranging%20%E2%80%9Clogistical%20support%20for%20anti-national%20activities%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cinciting%20violence%20thereby%20leading%20to%20disturbance%20in%20public%20order%E2%80%9D%20while%20terming%20him%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cthreat%20to%20public%20order.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20court%20quashed%20the%20PSA%20proceedings%20against%20him%2C%20Shah%20was%20arrested%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%E2%80%99s%20State%20Investigation%20Agency%20in%20the%20case%20in%20which%20he%20has%20now%20been%20granted%20bail.%20He%20has%20been%20granted%20bail%20in%20three%20other%20criminal%20cases%20brought%20against%20him%20by%20J%26amp%3BK%20Police%20for%20the%20reporting%20done%20by%20his%20magazine%20on%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShah%20was%20charged%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20May%202020%20over%20the%20coverage%20of%20a%20gun%20battle%20between%20militants%20and%20security%20forces%20in%20Srinagar.%20In%20the%20encounter%E2%80%99s%20aftermath%2C%20local%20residents%20had%20alleged%20that%20security%20forces%20took%20away%20their%20precious%20belongings%2C%20a%20charge%20denied%20by%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20allegations%20and%20the%20denial%20were%20widely%20reported%20by%20local%20and%20national%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20on%20January%2030%2C%202021%2C%20Shah%20was%20booked%20under%20Sections%20153%20(provocation%20with%20intent%20to%20cause%20riot)%20and%20505%20(statements%20conducive%20to%20public%20mischief)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20for%20a%20report%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20alleged%20that%20the%20Army%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpressuring%E2%80%9D%20the%20management%20of%20a%20private%20school%20in%20Shopian%20to%20organise%20the%20Republic%20Day%20celebrations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Army%20had%20denied%20the%20charge%20and%20proceeded%20to%20file%20a%20criminal%20case%20against%20Shah%2C%20who%20was%20later%20granted%20bail%20by%20a%20court.%20Shah%20has%20reportedly%20faced%20six%20cases%20of%20intimidation%20between%20June%202017%20and%20January%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20case%20pertains%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20coverage%20of%20a%20gun%20battle%20in%20south%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20Pulwama%20district%20in%20which%20three%20militants%2C%20including%20a%20top%20commander%2C%20were%20gunned%20down%20last%20year.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20accused%20of%20%E2%80%9Cglorifying%20terrorist%20activities%E2%80%9D%20and%20causing%20%E2%80%9Cdisaffection%20against%20the%20country%E2%80%9D%20by%20alleged%20%E2%80%9Cincorrect%20reporting%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2019%20this%20year%2C%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Electronics%20and%20Information%20Technology%20pulled%20down%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Kashmir%20Walla%3C%2Fem%3E%20website%20under%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Information%20and%20Technology%20Act%2C%202000%2C%20a%20controversial%20law%20which%20has%20been%20criticised%20by%20the%20free%20speech%20activists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPress%20freedom%20in%20India%20has%20suffered%20relentless%20blows%20in%20recent%20years%20under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%20According%20to%20the%20World%20Press%20Freedom%20Index%E2%80%99s%20latest%20report%2C%20India%20slipped%20to%20161%20out%20of%20180%20countries%20this%20year%2C%20losing%2011%20more%20spots%20as%20compared%20to%20the%202022%20ranking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Paris-based%20press%20freedom%20watchdog%20Reporters%20Without%20Borders%2C%20India%20has%20been%20using%20%E2%80%9Ccharges%20of%20defamation%2C%20sedition%2C%20contempt%20of%20court%20and%20endangering%20national%20security%20%E2%80%A6%20increasingly%20..%20against%20journalists%20critical%20of%20the%20government%2C%20who%20are%20branded%20as%20%E2%80%98anti-national%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%20The%20government%20has%20denied%20these%20charges%2C%20accusing%20the%20watchdog%20of%20%E2%80%9Csubverting%20the%20democratic%20freedoms%20all%20over%20the%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700293259000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F12194450%2Fimage-44.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fafter-nearly-2-years-jk-hc-grants-bail-to-kashmir-walla-editor-fahad-shah%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Shah%20was%20held%20on%20charges%20of%20terrorism%20for%20publishing%20the%20article%2C%20%E2%80%98The%20shackles%20of%20slavery%20will%20break%E2%80%99%2C%20in%20his%20now-defunct%20magazine%2C%20'The%20Kashmir%20Walla%2C'%20in%202011.%20The%20opinion%20piece%20was%20authored%2